						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the <hi rend="italic">kañchuguṁbha-gōpuram</hi> in the Narasiṁhasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Veṅkaṭapati, 1590 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1512 (current), Virōdhi, Phālguṇa ba. 30,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1590 A.D., March 25, (Wednesday).</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land for offerings during the processions of god Prahlādavarada at Diguva Tirupati by Savaram Raṅgapparāju, son of Yallaparāju and grandson of Sūraparāju of Mallapachintakuṇṭa.</p>						

						</summary>
